-- ECB funding to Greek banks drops slightly in July
-- 
-- Mon Aug 11, 2014 10:17AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, Aug 11 (Reuters) - European Central Bank (ECB) funding to Greek banks fell in July by 330 million euros, Greek central bank data showed on Monday.

ECB funding dropped to 44.62 billion euros ($59.74 billion) from 44.95 billion euros in June.